Razer has launched its new 15-inch and 17-inch Blade gaming notebooks, which boast Nvidia’s RTX Max Q graphics cards and impressive displays. The latest iteration of the Blade laptop lineup comprises the new Blade 15 which can be outfitted with a 4K OLED panel, and the Blade Pro 17, which boasts powerful specifications and a 144Hz panel. Each of these devices is available in various configurations, and can support up to an Nvidia GeForce RTX 2080 GPU for high-end graphics performance. Razer’s Blade laptops are CNC-milled from a single block of aircraft-grade aluminum and anodized with a matte finish to create a sleek and scratch-resistant exterior. The new laptops will be available from May 2019, and the Blade Pro 17 will be priced from $2,499 while the base model of the Razer Blade 15 will be priced from $1,999. Razer said the advanced Blade 15 model, which includes a 4K OLED display, will be priced from $2,399. Below are the maximum specifications for the new Razer Blade 15 and Blade 17 Pro. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-304030" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-15.jpg" alt="Razer Blade 15" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-15.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-15-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-15-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-304032" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-Pro-17.jpg" alt="Razer Blade Pro 17" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-Pro-17.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Razer-Blade-Pro-17-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/